[[Image:Winter_sun_on_Norwegian_mountain.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A mountain (large mass of rock)]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|montaigne|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|VL.}} *{{term||montanea}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|montanus|montānus|mountainous|lang=la}}, from {{term|mons|mōns|mountain|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈmaʊn.tɪn/}}, {{SAMPA|/"maUn.tIn/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈmaʊn.tən/}}
* {{audio|en-us-mountain.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|En-uk-mountain.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A large [[mass]] of [[earth]] and [[rock]], rising above the common level of the earth or adjacent land.
# A large [[amount]].
#: ''There's still a '''mountain''' of work to do.''

